Third-party components

Perch orchestrates and connects to third-party software that it pulls at run
time. It does not vendor or redistribute any third-party source code in this
repository. Each component remains under its own license, held by its respective
owner:

  * Container images for managed services (for example: Postgres with the
    pgvector extension, Redis, an S3-compatible object store, an auto-generated
    REST layer, and an identity service) are pulled from their official
    registries at run time.
  * Python dependency: PyYAML (MIT License).
  * The web console loads assets from public CDNs at run time, each under its own
    license -- e.g. the Inter and JetBrains Mono typefaces (SIL Open Font
    License 1.1) and utility CSS / icon fonts (MIT / Apache-2.0).

If you redistribute Perch, keep this NOTICE file with it (Apache-2.0 section 4d).
